//@version=6
// ============================================================================
// ORB SYMMETRIC v2 — ungated two-sided ORB + DYNAMIC $-RISK SIZING  MNQ/MGC 15m
// ============================================================================
// WHAT CHANGED vs orb_sym_v1 (and what deliberately did NOT)
//   ONE change: contract quantity. v1 traded a fixed 2 micros and skipped days
//   whose 2-contract risk exceeded $575. v2 defaults to DYNAMIC sizing:
//       qty = min( floor( riskBudgetUSD / (stopDistance x pointValue) ), maxQty )
//   so every trade risks ~the same dollars regardless of OR width (wide OR ->
//   fewer contracts, narrow OR -> more). Entries, exits, stops, targets, the
//   one-trade-per-day lock, session flat, costs, visuals: byte-identical to v1.
//   A "Fixed contracts" mode input reproduces v1 behavior exactly as fallback.
//
// WHY (validated 2026-07-05, reports/tweaks/01_prespec.md -> 03_verdict.md;
// pre-registered rule, real MNQ/MGC 15m data, costs on, same MC engine that
// picked the v1 config):
//   Cost-in-R is quantity-invariant, so avg_R/trade is unchanged BY
//   CONSTRUCTION — dynamic sizing only reshapes the daily $ distribution.
//   On the BOTH-symbols Tradeify 50k Lightning book, $300/leg budget:
//     P(first payout) 86.9% vs 80.3%  (fixed-2/$575, same engine)
//     EV/attempt      +$2,312 vs +$2,114 (higher under all fee/split combos)
//     worst both-legs day ~ -$609 vs -$1,150  (huge margin to the $1,250 DLL)
//     consistency rule binds on 0% of passing paths (vs 77% — max win/day
//       ~$600 both legs can't trip the consistency threshold; the ~10-day
//       "consistency tax" is gone)
//     trade-off: median days to first payout ~60 vs ~51 (smaller daily EV).
//   Budgets $400/$500/$575 FAILED the pre-registered gate (more busts).
//   Single-leg caution: B300 sizes MGC UP (median 3 micros) — MGC-ONLY at $300
//   tested WORSE (70.8% vs 88.5% pass). The win is a BOTH-book property.
//   Do not run MGC alone in dynamic mode without re-running the optimizer.
//
//   ALSO TESTED AND REFUTED THE SAME DAY (do not re-add):
//   - Close-confirmed exits (stop and/or target wait for candle close):
//     avg_R collapses (MGC edge -> ~0), losses reach -2.6R..-4.3R, Lightning
//     pass rate drops from 80% to ~50%, worst MC day grazes the $1,250 DLL.
//     Intrabar stop/limit exits are the validated mechanics. Full record in
//     reports/tweaks/. — And from the earlier scan: ALL 20 ICT/quant
//     confluence filters (sweeps, FVGs, killzones, PDH/PDL, midnight/weekly
//     open, NDOG/NWOG, rel. volume, VWAP, gap size, Monday, NR7, narrow OR,
//     overnight range/inventory, high-vol downsizing) — zero survived
//     (reports/confluence/04_verdict.md). No direction gates (permutation-
//     refuted). This strategy is deliberately filter-free: take every valid
//     signal, in whichever direction it breaks.
//
// THE TRADE (unchanged from v1, one decision per day):
//   Chart    : 15-minute, CME_MINI:MNQ1! or COMEX:MGC1! (continuous ticker).
//   OR       : 09:30-10:00 ET session window. Entry: first 15m CLOSE beyond
//              the OR (either side), 10:00-16:00 ET; first breakout locks day.
//   Stop     : opposite OR boundary.   Target : 1:1.   Flat at session end.
//
// BASE VALIDATION (per-trade edge, unchanged — see orb_sym_v1.pine header for
// the full record): MNQ +0.119R/trade (CI 0.089-0.150, n=1245), MGC +0.085R
// (CI 0.055-0.115, n=1801); fade-null negative, 1-bar-lag survives, all 10
// chronological folds positive.
//
// ALERTS: one alert, "Any alert() function call" — fires only when a real
// strategy order is placed (same bar it fills, entries are market-on-close).
// margin_long/short = 0 so the broker emulator never rejects a capped signal.
// Research / advisory only — NOT auto-trading.
//
// CHANGELOG:
//   2026-07-06 v2b: fixed SL/TP/entry line freeze reliability. The freeze that
//     stops a closed trade's extend=right lines was gated on catching a SINGLE
//     bar (position_size transitioning 0<-nonzero); if that exact bar was ever
//     missed the line kept extend=right forever with nothing left to clear it
//     (user-reported: some lines never timed out). Now fires on ANY flat bar
//     while the handles are still live (self-healing) and anchors x2 to the
//     trade's actual strategy.closedtrades exit bar instead of "this bar" (also
//     removes a pre-existing 1-bar cosmetic overshoot). DISPLAY ONLY: no
//     change to entries/exits/sizing/locks (re-audited, byte-identical decision
//     path). NOT TV-tested.
//   2026-07-05 v2a: dynamic $-risk sizing (default ON, $300/leg, max 10
//     micros) per reports/tweaks/03_verdict.md; fixed mode = v1 fallback.
//     Decision path (entries/exits/locks/flat) untouched from v1 build e.
//     NOT TV-TESTED.
// ============================================================================

strategy("ORB Symmetric v2 (MNQ/MGC 15m NY, dynamic size)",
     shorttitle = "ORB-SYM-v2",
     overlay = true,
     process_orders_on_close = true,
     calc_on_every_tick = false,
     initial_capital = 50000,
     default_qty_type = strategy.fixed,
     default_qty_value = 1,
     commission_type = strategy.commission.cash_per_contract,
     commission_value = 0.62,   // ~$1.24 RT/2 (MNQ); MGC ~$1.20 RT — matches the validated cost model
     slippage = 1,              // 1 tick per fill
     margin_long = 0, margin_short = 0,  // no emulator margin check: every signal under the
                                         // budget must fill, exactly like the validated sim
     max_lines_count = 500, max_labels_count = 500, max_boxes_count = 500)
// NOTE on drawings: TV keeps only the most recent ~500 line/label/box objects, so
// per-trade markers fade out in deep history. The SL/TP PLOT overlays and the OR
// plot lines have no such cap and follow the chart everywhere you scroll.

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// INPUTS
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
TZ = "America/New_York"

sizeMode = input.string("Dynamic $ budget", "Sizing mode",
     options = ["Dynamic $ budget", "Fixed contracts"],
     tooltip = "DYNAMIC (validated default, reports/tweaks/03_verdict.md): " +
               "qty = floor(budget / (stop distance x point value)), capped at " +
               "max contracts — every trade risks ~the same dollars. BOTH-book " +
               "50k Lightning: 86.9% first payout, median ~60 days, EV " +
               "+$2,312/attempt, worst both-legs day ~-$609, consistency tax " +
               "eliminated. FIXED reproduces orb_sym_v1 exactly (2ct, $575 cap).")
riskBudgetUSD = input.float(300.0, "Dynamic: $ risk budget per trade", minval = 50,
     tooltip = "Per chart/leg. $300 is the ONLY budget that passed the " +
               "pre-registered gate ($400/$500/$575 all bust more than they " +
               "gain). Running BOTH symbols: worst-case both-legs-stopped day " +
               "~ -2x budget = -$600 vs the $1,250 DLL. Do NOT raise without " +
               "re-running the optimizer (reports/tweaks/).")
maxQty = input.int(10, "Dynamic: max contracts (micros)", minval = 1, maxval = 40,
     tooltip = "Hard ceiling on the dynamic quantity (Tradeify 50k allows 40 " +
               "micros; 10 is the validated cap). Binds only on very narrow ORs.")
qtyFixed = input.int(2, "Fixed: contracts (micros)", minval = 1, maxval = 5,
     tooltip = "Used only in Fixed mode — v1's Lightning-optimized default.")
maxRiskUSD = input.float(575.0, "Fixed: max $ risk per trade (skip wider days)", minval = 50,
     tooltip = "Used only in Fixed mode — v1's cap. In Dynamic mode the budget " +
               "itself is the cap (a day is skipped only if even 1 contract " +
               "risks more than the budget).")
showPanel = input.bool(true, "Show diagnostic panel")

isDyn = sizeMode == "Dynamic $ budget"

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// SESSION + OPENING RANGE (window-defined; no clock arithmetic)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
inSess   = not na(time(timeframe.period, "0930-1600", TZ))
orActive = not na(time(timeframe.period, "0930-1000", TZ))
sessStart = inSess and not inSess[1]
sessEnd   = (not inSess) and inSess[1]

tfOK  = timeframe.isminutes and timeframe.multiplier == 15
isMNQ = str.contains(syminfo.ticker, "MNQ")
isMGC = not isMNQ and str.contains(syminfo.ticker, "MGC")
symOK = isMNQ or isMGC
cfgOK = tfOK and symOK

var float orHi = na
var float orLo = na
var bool  orSeen = false
var bool  locked = false
var int nSessions = 0
var int nEntries = 0
var int nRiskSkips = 0

// live-position state (display only — order levels are set at entry via strategy.exit)
var float posEntry = na
var float posStop  = na
var float posTgt   = na
var int   posSide  = 0
var int   posQty   = 0
// per-trade drawing handles
var line  lnEntry = na
var line  lnStop  = na
var line  lnTgt   = na
var box   orBox   = na

if sessStart
    orHi := na
    orLo := na
    orSeen := false
    locked := false
    nSessions += 1
if orActive
    orHi := na(orHi) ? high : math.max(orHi, high)
    orLo := na(orLo) ? low : math.min(orLo, low)
    orSeen := true

// OR is tradeable once the window has passed, this bar is still in-session,
// and the range is sane. No other conditions exist — by design.
orDone = inSess and not orActive and orSeen and not na(orHi) and orHi > orLo

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// ONE-SHOT SYMMETRIC BREAKOUT (decision path identical to v1; only qty differs)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
canTrade  = orDone and not locked and cfgOK and strategy.position_size == 0
longBrk   = canTrade and close > orHi
shortBrk  = canTrade and close < orLo

if longBrk or shortBrk
    side    = longBrk ? 1 : -1
    entryPx = close
    riskPts = longBrk ? entryPx - orLo : orHi - entryPx
    risk1cUSD = riskPts * syminfo.pointvalue
    qtyDyn  = risk1cUSD > 0 ? math.min(maxQty, math.floor(riskBudgetUSD / risk1cUSD)) : 0
    qtyUse  = isDyn ? qtyDyn : qtyFixed
    riskUSD = risk1cUSD * qtyUse
    sizeOK  = isDyn ? qtyUse >= 1 : riskUSD <= maxRiskUSD
    if riskPts > 0 and qtyUse >= 1 and sizeOK
        stopPx = entryPx - side * riskPts
        tgtPx  = entryPx + side * riskPts
        if longBrk
            strategy.entry("L", strategy.long, qty = qtyUse, comment = "OR-break long")
            strategy.exit("Lx", "L", stop = stopPx, limit = tgtPx)
        else
            strategy.entry("S", strategy.short, qty = qtyUse, comment = "OR-break short")
            strategy.exit("Sx", "S", stop = stopPx, limit = tgtPx)
        // ---- visual layer (display only, no order logic) ----
        posEntry := entryPx
        posStop  := stopPx
        posTgt   := tgtPx
        posSide  := side
        posQty   := qtyUse
        // clean lines only — no price labels; extend right so the levels are
        // unmissable ahead of price while the trade is live
        lnEntry := line.new(bar_index, entryPx, bar_index + 1, entryPx,
             color = color.new(color.gray, 20), style = line.style_dotted, width = 1,
             extend = extend.right)
        lnStop := line.new(bar_index, stopPx, bar_index + 1, stopPx,
             color = color.new(color.red, 0), style = line.style_solid, width = 3,
             extend = extend.right)
        lnTgt := line.new(bar_index, tgtPx, bar_index + 1, tgtPx,
             color = color.new(color.green, 0), style = line.style_solid, width = 3,
             extend = extend.right)
        linefill.new(lnEntry, lnTgt,  color.new(color.green, 88))   // reward zone
        linefill.new(lnEntry, lnStop, color.new(color.red, 90))     // risk zone
        nEntries += 1
        alert("ORB-SYM v2 " + (longBrk ? "LONG " : "SHORT ") + syminfo.ticker +
              " qty=" + str.tostring(qtyUse) + (isDyn ? " (dyn)" : " (fixed)") +
              " entry~" + str.tostring(entryPx, format.mintick) +
              " SL=" + str.tostring(stopPx, format.mintick) +
              " TP=" + str.tostring(tgtPx, format.mintick) +
              " risk$~" + str.tostring(riskUSD, "#") +
              " (signal = confirmed 15m close; fills lag)",
              alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
    else
        nRiskSkips += 1
        // skipped entry: the whole opening-range zone turns red for the day
        if not na(orBox)
            box.set_bgcolor(orBox, color.new(color.red, 82))
            box.set_border_color(orBox, color.new(color.red, 30))
    // ANY first breakout locks the day — including risk-skipped ones —
    // matching the validated one-decision-per-day simulation exactly.
    locked := true

// extend the live trade's lines while the position is open; stamp the result on exit.
// Freeze fires on ANY flat bar where the handles are still live (not only the single
// bar where position_size is first observed to transition to 0) -- self-healing against
// a missed transition bar (e.g. a data gap around a session boundary), which previously
// could leave a line's extend=right set forever with nothing left to clear it. Anchored
// to the trade's actual recorded exit bar via strategy.closedtrades, not "this bar", so
// the line stops exactly at the exit rather than wherever the flat check happened to fire.
if strategy.position_size != 0 and not na(lnStop)
    line.set_x2(lnEntry, bar_index)
    line.set_x2(lnStop, bar_index)
    line.set_x2(lnTgt, bar_index)
if strategy.position_size == 0 and not na(lnStop)
    exitBarIdx = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ?
         strategy.closedtrades.exit_bar_index(strategy.closedtrades - 1) : bar_index
    line.set_extend(lnEntry, extend.none), line.set_x2(lnEntry, exitBarIdx)
    line.set_extend(lnStop, extend.none),  line.set_x2(lnStop, exitBarIdx)
    line.set_extend(lnTgt, extend.none),   line.set_x2(lnTgt, exitBarIdx)
    lastPnl = strategy.closedtrades > 0 ?
         strategy.closedtrades.profit(strategy.closedtrades - 1) : 0.0
    label.new(bar_index, close,
         (lastPnl >= 0 ? "✔ +$" : "✘ −$") + str.tostring(math.abs(lastPnl), "#"),
         style = posSide == 1 ? label.style_label_down : label.style_label_up,
         color = lastPnl >= 0 ? color.new(color.green, 25) : color.new(color.red, 25),
         textcolor = color.white, size = size.small)
    posEntry := na
    posStop := na
    posTgt := na
    posSide := 0
    posQty := 0
    lnEntry := na
    lnStop := na
    lnTgt := na

// Force-flat at session end: pre-B7 mechanism only (see orb_sym_v1 header
// KNOWN OPEN ITEMS before touching this line).
if sessEnd and strategy.position_size != 0
    strategy.close_all(comment = "session flat")

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// VISUALS + PANEL
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// OR box: shaded while forming, frozen once complete (drawing — fades in deep history)
if orActive and na(orBox)
    orBox := box.new(bar_index, high, bar_index, low,
         bgcolor = color.new(color.blue, 88), border_color = color.new(color.blue, 40))
if orActive and not na(orBox)
    box.set_rightbottom(orBox, bar_index, orLo)
    box.set_top(orBox, orHi)
if sessStart
    orBox := na

// OR levels as PLOTS — uncapped, follow the chart into deep history
plot(orDone ? orHi : na, "OR high", color = color.new(color.teal, 0),  style = plot.style_linebr)
plot(orDone ? orLo : na, "OR low",  color = color.new(color.maroon, 0), style = plot.style_linebr)

// live SL/TP as PLOTS while a position is open (uncapped backup to the lines)
inPos = strategy.position_size != 0
plot(inPos ? posStop : na, "Stop (live)",   color = color.new(color.red, 30),
     style = plot.style_linebr, linewidth = 2)
plot(inPos ? posTgt : na,  "Target (live)", color = color.new(color.green, 30),
     style = plot.style_linebr, linewidth = 2)
plot(inPos ? posEntry : na, "Entry (live)", color = color.new(color.gray, 40),
     style = plot.style_linebr)

// entry arrows — plotshapes are uncapped and survive full history
plotshape(nEntries > nEntries[1] and posSide == 1,  "Long entry",  style = shape.triangleup,
     location = location.belowbar, color = color.new(color.green, 0), size = size.normal,
     text = "LONG", textcolor = color.new(color.green, 0))
plotshape(nEntries > nEntries[1] and posSide == -1, "Short entry", style = shape.triangledown,
     location = location.abovebar, color = color.new(color.red, 0), size = size.normal,
     text = "SHORT", textcolor = color.new(color.red, 0))

bgcolor(orActive ? color.new(color.blue, 92) : na)

var table pnl = table.new(position.top_right, 2, 6, border_width = 1)
if showPanel and barstate.islast
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 0, "Config"), table.cell(pnl, 1, 0,
         (tfOK ? "15m OK" : "WRONG TF — NEED 15m") + " / " +
         (isMNQ ? "MNQ" : isMGC ? "MGC" : "UNSUPPORTED SYMBOL"),
         text_color = cfgOK ? color.gray : color.red,
         bgcolor = cfgOK ? na : color.new(color.red, 80))
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 1, "Sizing"), table.cell(pnl, 1, 1,
         isDyn ? "DYNAMIC $" + str.tostring(riskBudgetUSD, "#") + "/trade, max " +
              str.tostring(maxQty) + "ct" + (posQty > 0 ? " (live: " + str.tostring(posQty) + "ct)" : "") :
              "FIXED " + str.tostring(qtyFixed) + "ct, cap $" + str.tostring(maxRiskUSD, "#"))
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 2, "Status"), table.cell(pnl, 1, 2,
         not cfgOK ? "CONFIG ERROR — NO TRADES WILL FIRE" :
         locked ? "LOCKED (day done)" : orDone ? "ARMED" : orActive ? "OR FORMING" : "OFF-SESSION",
         text_color = cfgOK ? color.gray : color.red)
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 3, "Sessions / entries / risk-skips"),
         table.cell(pnl, 1, 3, str.tostring(nSessions) + " / " + str.tostring(nEntries) + " / " + str.tostring(nRiskSkips))
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 4, "Entry rate (expect ~0.7/session)"),
         table.cell(pnl, 1, 4, nSessions > 0 ? str.tostring(nEntries / float(nSessions), "#.##") : "-")
    table.cell(pnl, 0, 5, "Net profit"),
         table.cell(pnl, 1, 5, str.tostring(strategy.netprofit, "#.##"),
         text_color = strategy.netprofit >= 0 ? color.green : color.red)
